titlestmt.titleproper: Inventory of the Raymond Benjamin West papers, 1901-1918

publicationstmt.publisher: University of Wyoming. American Heritage Center.

profiledesc.creation: Finding aid encoded by Ann Mulfort December 2012

repository.label: Repository
repository.corpname: University of Wyoming. American Heritage Center.

bioghist.head: Biography of Raymond Benjamin West
bioghist.p: Raymond Benjamin West (1875- ) was a lawyer in Basin, Wyoming.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Content
scopecontent.p: Collection consists of correspondence regarding court cases (1901-1918) and West's extensive legal files of court cases dealing with water rights, mining and petroleum companies and the collection of debts (1904-1918).

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: There are no access restrictions on the materials for research purposes, and the collection is open to the public.

userestrict.head: Copyright Information
userestrict.p: The researcher assumes full responsibility for observing all copyright, property, and libel laws as they apply.

relatedmaterial.head: Related Materials
relatedmaterial.p: There are no known other archival collections created by Raymond Benjamin West at the date of processing.

acqinfo.head: Acquisition Information
acqinfo.p: The collection was received from Mrs. W.A. Towne in 1946.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: The finding aid was encoded by Morgan Walsh and D. Claudia Thompson in 2020.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Item Description, Box Number, Folder Number, Collection Name, Collection Number, American Heritage Center, University of Wyoming.
